Achong is better known for playing cricket.  He was mainly a bowler.  His stock ball was left-arm orthodox spin (left-arm finger spin), but one of his variations was unorthodox left-arm spin.  After bowling this variation to have Walter Robins stumped at Old Trafford in 1933, it is reputed that Robins said to the umpire Joe Hardstaff Sr., \fancy being done by a bloody Chinaman\".  Learie Constantine is said to have replied: \"Do you mean the bowler or the ball?\"  An unorthodox left-arm spin delivery (spinning from the off side to the leg side for a right-handed batsman) is known as a \"chinaman\" as a result.  However